# Examples

## Example 1:
Input:
```
### Added files:
[src/main.py, README.md, config.json]

### Deleted files:
[old/unused.py]

### Modified files:
[utils.py]

### current .gitignore Content
(empty)
```
Expected Output:
```
(empty — output nothing)
```

## Example 2:
Input:
```
### Added files:
[pycache/main.cpython-310.pyc, dist/app.js, .env.local, .vscode/settings.json]

### Deleted files:
[]

### Modified files:
[]

### current .gitignore Content
*.log
```
Expected Output:
```
# Compiled and build artifacts
*.pyc
__pycache__/
*.o
*.obj
dist/
build/

# Dependencies
.venv/
venv/
node_modules/

# Logs and temp files
*.log
*.tmp
*.swp

# Environment
.env
.env.local
.env.*

# Editors
.vscode/
.idea/

# Original rules preserved
*.log
```
# Dependencies
node_modules/
venv/
.venv/
__pycache__/
.mypy_cache/
.pytest_cache/
dist/
build/
target/
.gradle/

# OS generated files
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db

# Compiled files
*.pyc
*.class
*.o
*.exe
*.dll
*.so
*.a
*.obj
*.out

# Coverage
coverage/
htmlcov/
.coverage

# Compressed files
*.zip
*.gz
*.tar
*.tgz
*.bz2
*.xz
*.7z
*.rar
*.zst
*.lz4
*.lzh
*.cab
*.arj
*.rpm
*.deb
*.Z
*.lz
*.lzo
*.tar.gz
*.tar.bz2
*.tar.xz
*.tar.zst
```
Nothing needs to be added to .gitignore since the changes only include HTML and JavaScript source files which should be tracked in version control.
